please s. http://wiki.niftylight.de/libniftyled first



============
Requirements
============

To compile libniftyled from source, you need the following:

* automake
* autoconf
* libtool
* gcc
* pkg-config



============================
Example compile instructions
============================

To prepare build, run the following commands in the release directory:

$ autoreconf -i
$ ./configure --prefix=/usr

To compile, run:
$ make

To install, run:
$ su
[Password]
$ make check
$ make install


==========
Developers
==========

Configure options
-----------------

--disable-debug  - use to not compile for debugging
--disable-tests  - use to not compile tests


------------
Make targets
------------

make check      - run tests
make distcheck  - create tarball-archive after successfull checks
make indent     - indent sources according to the conventions in .indent.pro



========
See also
========

* INSTALL.fsf on more generic installation-instructions
* http://wiki.niftylight.de


